{"id":99482,"date":"2018-01-01T07:00:20","date_gmt":"2018-01-01T12:00:20","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/techvibes.com\/?p=99482"},"modified":"2017-12-20T13:36:59","modified_gmt":"2017-12-20T18:36:59","slug":"how-canada-watched-netflix-in-2017","status":"publish","type":"magazine","link":"https:\/\/brainstation.io\/magazine\/how-canada-watched-netflix-in-2017","title":{"rendered":"How Canada Watched Netflix in 2017 and Became Global Binging Leaders"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>New Year\u2019s Day was the most popular day to stream Netflix in Canada, kicking off what would become a record-setting year, according to new data from\u00a0the streaming service.<\/p>\n<p>In 2017, Canadians were crowned the global leaders when it comes to Netflix binge racing\u2013a term that describes speeding through a full season in less than 24 hours after the show\u2019s release. Netflix has found that Canada is also one of the top countries for binge-watching, ranking second globally for having the most members to watch shows back-to-back-to-back on Netflix every single day.<\/p>\n<p>One of those dedicated viewers\u00a0in Canada had a certain fondness for a fantasy series about a ring. Whether they are obsessed with Middle-Earth or simply left the film on for their dog, one Canadian watched Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King 361 times in the past year. With only the extended version hosted on Netflix, the trilogy&#8217;s finale clocks in at 4 hours and 23 minutes. They were edged out by one global user in particular who watched Pirates of the Caribbean: The Curse of the Black Pearl 365 days in a row\u2014impressive or obsessive?<\/p>\n<p>Netflix broke down what newly released shows\u00a0were \u2018devoured\u2019 by Canadians this year, defined by shows watched for more than two hours a day, and what titles streamers \u2018savoured,\u2019 watching for two hours or less in one sitting.<\/p>\n<p>In Canada, the top five shows Netflix users devoured were\u00a0Greenleaf,\u00a0American Vandal,\u00a0Suburra: Blood on Rome,\u00a0Gilmore Girls: A Year in the Life, and Ingobernable.<\/p>\n<p>The top five shows Netflix users savoured were\u00a0The Crown,\u00a0Neo Yokio,\u00a0Wet Hot American Summer: Ten Years Later,\u00a0Ozark and\u00a0A Series of Unfortunate Events.<\/p>\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-99501\" src=\"https:\/\/wpassets.brainstation.io\/app\/uploads\/2017\/12\/13095819\/Netflix_2.png\" alt=\"Netflix_2\" width=\"1440\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wpassets.brainstation.io\/app\/uploads\/2017\/12\/13095819\/Netflix_2.png 1440w, https:\/\/wpassets.brainstation.io\/app\/uploads\/2017\/12\/13095819\/Netflix_2-300x167.png 300w, https:\/\/wpassets.brainstation.io\/app\/uploads\/2017\/12\/13095819\/Netflix_2-768x427.png 768w, https:\/\/wpassets.brainstation.io\/app\/uploads\/2017\/12\/13095819\/Netflix_2-1024x569.png 1024w, https:\/\/wpassets.brainstation.io\/app\/uploads\/2017\/12\/13095819\/Netflix_2-1280x711.png 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1440px) 100vw, 1440px\" \/><\/h3>\n<p>The streaming service also surveyed Canadian Netflix\u00a0streamers to find out what shows they watched ahead of their partners, proving the highly anticipated new season of Orange is the New Black was\u00a0just too addictive to turn off. When Canadians did watch together, the most popular shows were Stranger Things and Riverdale.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-99502\" src=\"https:\/\/wpassets.brainstation.io\/app\/uploads\/2017\/12\/13095819\/Netflix_1.png\" alt=\"Netflix_1\" width=\"1440\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wpassets.brainstation.io\/app\/uploads\/2017\/12\/13095819\/Netflix_1.png 1440w, https:\/\/wpassets.brainstation.io\/app\/uploads\/2017\/12\/13095819\/Netflix_1-300x167.png 300w, https:\/\/wpassets.brainstation.io\/app\/uploads\/2017\/12\/13095819\/Netflix_1-768x427.png 768w, https:\/\/wpassets.brainstation.io\/app\/uploads\/2017\/12\/13095819\/Netflix_1-1024x569.png 1024w, https:\/\/wpassets.brainstation.io\/app\/uploads\/2017\/12\/13095819\/Netflix_1-1280x711.png 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1440px) 100vw, 1440px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Earlier this year, Netflix also released new data about what series were the fastest to be binged. It really can\u2019t get more Canadian than this: the Nova Scotia-based mockumentary the Trailer Park Boys was the quickest binged newly released show in 2017. Newfoundlanders were found to be the fastest watchers in the country too.<\/p>\n<p>Whether it&#8217;s the country&#8217;s binge-racing title or a commitment to Canadian-made content, Netflix is taking a big bet on Canada,\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/borndigital.com\/2017\/10\/11\/netflix-and-explain-what-a-500-million-investment-actually-means\" target=\"_blank\">investing<\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\u00a0$500 million to produce original content in the country over the next five years.<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>New Year\u2019s Day was the most popular day to stream Netflix in Canada, kicking off what would become a record-setting year, according to new data from\u00a0the streaming service. In 2017, Canadians were crowned the global leaders when it comes to Netflix binge racing\u2013a term that describes speeding through a full season in less than 24 &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/brainstation.io\/magazine\/how-canada-watched-netflix-in-2017\">Continued<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":76241,"featured_media":99508,"menu_order":0,"template":"","meta":[],"categories":[13],"tags":[1744,2350,57,1745],"magazine-series":[],"magazine-region":[],"magazine-topic":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/brainstation.io\/wp\/api\/wp\/v2\/magazine\/99482"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/brainstation.io\/wp\/api\/wp\/v2\/magazine"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/brainstation.io\/wp\/api\/wp\/v2\/types\/magazine"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/brainstation.io\/wp\/api\/wp\/v2\/users\/76241"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\